<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="242" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">von Holleben</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-02-27"><hi rend="italic">February 27,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 208.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I beg to thank you for your
                            kindness and courtesy in communicating to me this morning, through Baron
                            Sternburg, information as to the intention of the Prussian Government in
                            sending agents here to settle questions of the management of insurance
                            companies in Prussia.</p>
                        <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>